This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with textual adversarial attacks and sentiment analysis, which are both related to natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it proposes a novel attack model that uses a particle swarm optimization algorithm. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because it deals with the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it proposes a new optimization algorithm for generating adversarial examples.
